Turkey Equity Movers: Baticim Bati, Petkim Petrokimya Are Active

-- B y   A y d a n   E k s i n
-- 
2011-05-05T15:15:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-05/turkish-equity-movers-baticim-batisoke-petkim-are-active.html
Turkey ’s benchmark  ISE National 100
Index (XU100)  fell 62.66, or 0.1 percent, to 69,374.88 at 5:30 p.m. when
trading ended in Istanbul.  The following stocks were active. Symbols are in
parentheses.  Baticim Bati Anadolu Cimento Sanayii AS (BTCIM)  , the
cement producer based in Izmir in western Turkey, surged 1.04
liras, or 11 percent, to 10.12 liras, gaining for a sixth day.
Its unit Baticim Enerji Elektrik Uretim AS was invited by
Turkey’s asset sales agency to buy two plants with a combined
59.5 megawatts capacity in southern Turkey by a July 4 deadline,
according to statements to the bourse yesterday. The company can
also buy three smaller plants from the agency, Baticim said.  Petkim Petrokimya Holding AS (PETKM)  : Turkey’s biggest
petrochemicals producer gained 7 kurus, or 2.6 percent, to 2.75
liras. First-quarter net income almost quadrupled from a year
earlier to 77.2 million liras ($50 million), Petkim said in a
statement to the bourse after the market closed yesterday. The
profit exceeded estimates compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Aydan Eksin in Istanbul at 
 aeksin@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
